  "prompt": "What is the most underrated romantic movie?",
  "response": "One often considered underrated is \"Before Sunrise\" (1995), directed by Richard Linklater. While it has garnered a devoted following, it doesn't always receive the widespread recognition it deserves compared to more mainstream romantic films. The film follows two young travelers, Jesse and C\u00e9line, who meet on a train in Europe and spend a night together in Vienna, exploring the city and sharing deep conversations. Its focus on genuine connection and the passage of time resonates with many viewers, making it a poignant exploration of love and human connection. If you haven't seen it, it might be worth a watch!",
